# Project: (your project name)
# (what this project does)

# Tech Stack
# - Backend: (e.g., FastAPI, Django, Express)
# - Frontend: (e.g., React, Next.js, Vue)
# - Database: (e.g., PostgreSQL, Supabase, Neon)
# - Deployment: (e.g., Vercel, Fly.io, AWS)

# Rules

Read files before modifying them - understand existing code before making changes
Use existing patterns - match the codebase's style, naming conventions, and architecture
Prefer editing over creating - modify existing files rather than creating new ones
Keep changes minimal - only change what's necessary to complete the task
No security vulnerabilities - avoid XSS, SQL injection, command injection, etc.
Handle errors gracefully - don't leave code in broken states
Test your changes - verify code works before marking task complete
Document non-obvious code - add comments only where the logic isn't self-evident
Every PR must reference a ticket - PR titles must include the ticket ID (e.g. "PROJ-123: Add feature")
Every ticket must have labels - at minimum one type label (Bug/Feature/Chore/Refactor), one risk label (Low Risk/Medium Risk/High Risk), and one area label (Frontend/Backend/Infra/Docs)
Set parent/child relationships for related tickets - use --parent when creating sub-tasks
Use blocking links for dependencies - the prerequisite ticket blocks the dependent ticket

# Available Labels
# Type: Bug, Feature, Chore, Refactor
# Risk: Low Risk, Medium Risk, High Risk
# Area: Frontend, Backend, Infra, Docs
# Special: HUMAN, Milestone, Blocked

# Ticket Discipline
Every ticket must have type and area labels. Every PR title must include the ticket ID. Use --parent for sub-tasks and bin/ticket relate for blocking.

# Avoid

Do not: Guessing file contents without reading them first
Do not: Creating new abstractions for one-time operations
Do not: Adding features, refactoring, or "improvements" beyond what was asked
Do not: Over-engineering with unnecessary complexity
Do not: Leaving console.log or debug statements in production code
Do not: Ignoring existing error handling patterns
Do not: Making assumptions about requirements without asking
Do not: Committing secrets, API keys, or credentials
Do not: Creating tickets without labels - every ticket needs type, risk, and area labels
Do not: Opening PRs without a ticket reference in the title
Do not: Creating related tickets without parent/child or blocking relationships

# Available Commands

# doctor: bin/vibe doctor
# setup: bin/vibe setup
# do: bin/vibe do <ticket-id>
# ticket list: bin/ticket list [OPTIONS]
# ticket get: bin/ticket get <ticket-id> [OPTIONS]
# ticket create: bin/ticket create "<title>" [OPTIONS]
# ticket update: bin/ticket update <ticket-id> [OPTIONS]
# ticket close: bin/ticket close <ticket-id> [--cancel]
# ticket comment: bin/ticket comment <ticket-id> "<message>"
# ticket relate: bin/ticket relate <ticket-id> [OPTIONS]
# ticket labels: bin/ticket labels [--json]
# ticket projects: bin/ticket projects [OPTIONS]
# ticket project: bin/ticket project <create|get> "<name>" [OPTIONS]
# ticket users: bin/ticket users [--json]
# ticket batch create: bin/ticket batch create --from <yaml-file> [--dry-run]
# ticket batch assign-project: bin/ticket batch assign-project --from <yaml-file> [--dry-run]
# ticket create-human-followup: bin/ticket create-human-followup [--parent <ticket-id>] [--files <file>...]
# pr: bin/vibe pr
# figma analyze: bin/vibe figma analyze
# generate-agent-instructions: bin/vibe generate-agent-instructions

# Workflows
# Starting Work on a Ticket:
#   bin/vibe do PROJ-123
#   bin/ticket get PROJ-123
#   git add <files>
#   git commit -m "PROJ-123: Brief description of changes"
#   git push -u origin PROJ-123
#   bin/vibe pr --title "PROJ-123: Add feature description"
# Creating Related Tickets:
#   bin/ticket create "Epic: User auth system" --description "Full authentication system with OAuth2." --label Feature --label Backend
#   bin/ticket create "Add login endpoint" --description "POST /auth/login with JWT." --label Feature --label Backend --parent PROJ-100
#   bin/ticket create "Add signup form" --description "React signup form component." --label Feature --label Frontend --parent PROJ-100
#   bin/ticket relate PROJ-101 --blocks PROJ-102
# Creating a Pull Request:
#   git status
#   git diff origin/main
#   git push -u origin BRANCH-NAME
#   bin/vibe pr
# Handling CI Failures:
#   gh pr checks <pr-number>
#   gh run view <run-id> --log-failed
#   git add <files>
#   git commit -m "Fix CI failure: <description>"
#   git push
# Cleaning Up After Merge:
#   git worktree remove <worktree-path>
#   git branch -d PROJ-123
#   bin/vibe doctor
